name: Il poker d'assi dello sci azzurro!
Una grande eccitante avventura di Aquila!

description: Pirates are the theme this issue as Richie Rich GEMS is proud to present MORE of the original adventures of Richie Rich the poor little rich boy. Richie Rich creator Sid Jacobson & artist Ernie Colon start things off with a brand new ‘Classic Style’ Richie story, “The Perilous Pirates of Bony Island”. And it’s followed by digitally re-colored classic stories “Pirates”, “Talk of the Season” and more! And there is even another of the ‘All New’ adventures of RICH RESCUE!
name: The Perilous Pirates of Bony Island; Big Splash; Pirates; Sound of Money; Buried Treasure; What a Catch; Talk of the Season; Big Tip; Give a Dog a Bone

description: Thrill to these classic tales of the Forgotten Realms, selected by creator Ed Greenwood! First, a thrilling 2-part adventure—adapted from Greenwood's own story “Elminster at the Magefair”! Plus two classic, genre-busting Forgotten Realms comics from the 1990s: "Head Cheeeese", in which the halfling Foxy battles a very case of... er, food poisoning? And a very unusual peek behind the curtain in "Everybody Wants to Run the Realms."
name: Elminster at the Magefair; Head Cheeeese; Everybody Wants to Run the Realms

volume.name: Dungeons and Dragons: Forgotten Realms - 100 Page Spectacular

description: Jack Pumpkinhead and Cheshire Cat came to our world to see how wonderful and mad it really was. Instead, they must rescue the White Knight from a secret society bent on 'removing' otherworldly creatures! Also features back-up stories that reunite writer Ben Avery with artists Mike Miller and Hector Sevilla.

volume.name: The Oz/Wonderland Chronicles: Jack & Cat Tales

description: Jack Pumpkinhead and Cheshire Cat discover there is more to Mae's books than they first thought, just as Patchwork Girl is captured by the secret group collecting the otherworldly creatures. And, the whereabouts of the Mad Hatter are revealed! Pencils by Russ Manning Award-nominee, Marc Borstel, along with Rick Mays (Gen13, Zatanna) and Matt Martin (Snowman, Anna Mercury)!

volume.name: The Oz/Wonderland Chronicles: Jack & Cat Tales

description: The adventures of Jack Pumpkinhead, Cheshire Cat, and their human friend Mae come to an explosive conclusion as they confront the mysterious enemy who has been hunting the visitors from other worlds. Plus, a revelation about the Wizard of Oz and his connection to these events.

volume.name: The Oz/Wonderland Chronicles: Jack & Cat Tales
